    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>After entering PIN and initiating a transaction, if the user minimizes the app and waits for some time, then reopens the app, an <b>“Error Occurred”</b> message is displayed.</p>

<p>However, the transaction is actually processed successfully in the backend. Additionally, when the user tries to perform the same transaction again, the system prevents it as a <b>duplicate transaction</b>.</p>

<p>This indicates a mismatch between the <b>frontend app state</b> and the <b>backend transaction status</b>.</p>

<h3><a name="StepstoReproduce"></a><b>Steps to Reproduce</b></h3>

<ol>
	<li>Initiate a transaction</li>
	<li>Enter PIN and proceed</li>
	<li>Minimize the app immediately</li>
	<li>Wait for a few seconds</li>
	<li>Reopen the app</li>
	<li>Observe the error message</li>
	<li>Retry same transaction → blocked as duplicate</li>
</ol>


<h3><a name="ExpectedBehavior"></a><b>Expected Behavior</b></h3>

<ul>
	<li>App should correctly sync transaction status after resume.</li>
	<li>If transaction is successful, a <b>success confirmation</b> should be shown.</li>
	<li>No misleading error message should appear.</li>
</ul>


<h3><a name="ActualBehavior"></a><b>Actual Behavior</b></h3>

<ul>
	<li>App shows <b>“Error Occurred”</b> after resuming from background.</li>
	<li>Transaction is actually <b>successful</b>.</li>
	<li>Retry attempt is blocked as <b>duplicate transaction</b>.</li>
</ul>


<h3><a name="Severity"></a><b>Severity</b></h3>

<p>High</p>
            <br/>
        </td>
